# System Content Implementation Summary

## What Was Implemented

We've successfully added the ability to mark tracks as **system content** from the Trike Library. These tracks are non-editable and display with a special locked badge.

---

## Database Changes (Already Completed)

```sql
-- Add is_system_content field to tracks table
ALTER TABLE tracks 
ADD COLUMN is_system_content BOOLEAN DEFAULT false NOT NULL;

-- Create index for fast queries
CREATE INDEX idx_tracks_system_content ON tracks(is_system_content);

-- Mark demo tracks as system content
UPDATE tracks 
SET is_system_content = true 
WHERE id IN (...);
```

---

## Code Changes (Completed)

### 1. TypeScript Types (`/lib/crud/tracks.ts`)
- Added `is_system_content?: boolean` to `CreateTrackInput` interface
- Added field to insert statement in `createTrack()` function
- Default value: `false` for user-created tracks

### 2. UI Display (`/components/ContentLibrary.tsx`)
- Added `Lock` icon import from lucide-react
- **Grid View**: Shows lock icon badge next to track title
- **List View**: Shows "Trike Library" badge next to track title
- **Detail View**: Shows "Trike Library" badge in header badges area
- Badge styling: Amber background (`bg-amber-100 text-amber-800`)

